IRS990.Desc: WEST CECIL HEALTH CENTER IS A FEDERALLY QUALIFIED HEALTH CARE CENTER THAT PROVIDES PRIMARY MEDICAL CARE, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES, DENTAL SERVICES AND GYNECOLOGICAL SERVICES AT THREE LOCATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WEST CECIL HEALTH CENTER HAD NO LIABILITY FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS. THE CENTER'S FEDERAL EXEMPT ORGANIZATION RETURNS ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE IRS, GENERALLY FOR A PERIOD OF THREE YEARS AFTER THE RETURNS ARE FILED.
NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTIONS IS THE NUMBER OF ITEMS DONATED

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CFO, CEO AND THE FINANCE COMMITTEE REVIEW AND DISCUSS A DRAFT OF THE FORM 990 AND PRESENT A RECOMMENDATION FOR APPROVAL FROM THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE BOARD WILL REVIEW AND DISCUSS THE FORM 990 BEFORE VOTING TO ACCEPT. ONCE APPROVED BY THE BOARD, THE FORM 990 IS FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ON AN ANNUAL BASIS, ALL BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT, INDICATING THAT THEY HAVE NO KNOWN CONFLICTS. IF A BOARD MEMBER BELIEVES HE OR SHE HAS A POTENTIAL CONFLICT, IT IS IMMEDIATELY BROUGHT TO THE ATTENTION OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE FOR THE APPROPRIATE RESOLUTION OF THE CONFLICT. THE SIGNED CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS ARE REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE FOR COMPLIANCE. AS AN ADDITIONAL MEASURE, THE ORGANIZATION SCREENS ALL VENDORS IN AN EFFORT TO AVOID ANY TRANSACTION THAT MAY INVOLVE BOARD MEMBERS, OFFICERS, OTHER MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL AND EMPLOYEES AND/OR THEIR RESPECTIVE FAMILY MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS MEETS ANNUALLY TO REVIEW AND DISCUSS THE CEO'S PERFORMANCE FOR THE PREVIOUS YEAR BASED ON OBJECTIVES SET FORTH FROM THE PREVIOUS YEAR. THE CEO IS EVALUATED ON THE FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE, AS WELL AS ON EMPLOYEE SATISFACTION, QUALITY METRICS AND PROGRESS TOWARDS MEETING THE ORGANIZATION'S STRATEGIC PLAN. THE COMPENSATION OF OTHER OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES IS DETERMINED BY THE CEO, BASED ON AN ANNUAL REVIEW PROCESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CENTER MAKES IT GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FORM 990 AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
THE PROCESS FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
